attack_permission

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
attack_permission -   attack_permission function, added for use by the allow_attack simul.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int attack_permission(object ob1,
                      object ob2,
                      string stringy)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^object%^RESET%^ - The person performing the action
%^BOLD%^object%^RESET%^ - The object being acted on, this object usually.
%^BOLD%^string%^RESET%^ - Attack type, this will be one of "combat", "theft", or "magic",
this lets you give your NPCs different responses for different attacks. As well
as make them immune to theft and magic (as an example)
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
int 1 if the action is denied, 0 is it can go through..EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/obj/monster.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5


attack_permission function, added for use by the allow_attack simul.
.EP

